This confirms that the main issue is not demand, but the ability of businesses to respond effectively to that demand.

\subsection{System Evaluation and Risks}

Several risks were identified during the analysis. One of the main risks is the variability in customer behavior, which makes demand difficult to predict.

Another challenge is reduced customer spending, which directly affects sales performance.

There is also resistance from some business owners to adopt new technologies or share their data.

To address these challenges, the system includes strategies such as predictive analysis, targeted promotions, and user training.

\section{Conclusions}

This work analyzed the challenges faced by small businesses in shopping malls in a post-pandemic context, focusing on the relationship between customer behavior and business performance. The results confirm that the main limitation is not the absence of customers, but the lack of structured and accessible information that allows businesses to respond effectively to demand.

Through the data collected, it was possible to identify key issues such as low conversion rates, inefficient inventory management, and a mismatch between customer expectations and product availability. Customers are present in shopping malls, but their needs are not always satisfied, which leads to lost sales opportunities.

The proposed data-driven system addresses these challenges by integrating customer behavior, environmental variables, and business data into a unified platform. This approach allows business owners to make more informed decisions, improve inventory control, and better adapt to changing market conditions.

Additionally, the system incorporates practical considerations such as usability, scalability, and data security, making it suitable for real-world implementation. Features such as inventory alerts, customer traffic analysis, and product recommendations provide direct value to small businesses.

However, the effectiveness of the system depends on data availability and user adoption. Without consistent data input and active participation from business owners, the system’s performance may be limited. Addressing these challenges requires both technical solutions and organizational strategies.

Future work should focus on implementing the system in real environments and evaluating its impact using measurable indicators such as sales performance, customer satisfaction, and inventory efficiency. The integration of predictive models and more advanced analytics could further enhance the system’s capabilities and long-term impact.

